## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of data and the inherent complexity of isolating the effects of trickle-down policies from other economic factors. Additionally, while the studies reviewed provide strong evidence against the efficacy of trickle-down economics, economic outcomes can be influenced by a multitude of variables, making it challenging to attribute changes solely to these policies. Further research could explore the long-term impacts of alternative economic policies that focus on income redistribution and support for lower-income groups.